The 2020 @realdonaldtrump "No Apologies" Tour continues: Not content with defending monuments to secessionists and slave traders, Trump signaled on Monday that he favors using the Confederate flag at sporting events. He did so in a tweet that attempted to shame Bubba Wallace, the

only Black NASCAR driver. Mr. Wallace’s pit crew found a noose in his newly assigned racing stall and assumed (incorrectly) that it was meant as an intimidation tactic against Mr. Wallace, who had recently voiced opposition to the use of the Confederate flag at NASCAR events.

NASCAR fans and rallied to Bubba’s defense before it was revealed that the noose had been in that stall for two years. Complicated? You bet. But Trump cut through the complexity by slamming Bubba and praising the Confederate flag. Trump tweeted Has BubbaWallace apologized to all

of those great NASCAR drivers & officials who came to his aid, stood by his side, & were willing to sacrifice everything for him, only to find out that the whole thing was just another HOAX? That & Flag decision has caused lowest ratings EVER!

While Trump’s tweets are never a model of clarity, one reading of the tweet suggests that he favors the use of Confederate flags at NASCAR races because it helps television ratings. Even the double-talking White House Press Secretary, Kayleigh McEnany, couldn’t come up with

enough spin to defend Trump’s tweet. See The Week, “White House claims Trump's Confederate flag tweet was taken 'out of context,' but won't clarify his position.” See also, Talking Points Memo, “WH Struggles To Explain Trump’s Tweet Seemingly Defending Confederate Flag.”
